description: {"blocks":[{"key":"72tp2","text":"This protocol describes the preparation of brain slices, setup of the electrophysiology rig, and solutions for collecting whole-cell recordings.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

funders.funder_name: Aligning Science Across Parkinson’s through the Michael J. Fox Foundation for Parkinson’s Research (MJFF)

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"bjmmo","text":"First prepare a 10x stock aCSF solution by fist add about 200 mL of ddH20 water into a clean 2L flask. Then add each of the following powders:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2su0t","text":"§NaCl: 1250 mM","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":7,"length":7}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"97pja","text":"§KCl: 25 mM","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":6,"length":5}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7hd0h","text":"§NaHCO3: 250 mM","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":9,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8flu6","text":"§NaH2PO4: 12.5 mM","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":10,"length":7}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4q5rh","text":"Next, fill the flask approximately three quarters with ddH2O and using a magnetic stirrer, allow the solution to be thoroughly dissolved. The mixed solution should then be brought to a final 2L volume and stored in a 2L glass bottle and refrigerated at 4°C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aslrj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6u8lj","text":"Note: the 10x stock aCSF can be used for up to a month and should be remade fresh after that time.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"arkgs","text":"Prepare 1 liter of 1X aCSF (to be used as both perfusate and cutting solution): ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9p0m9","text":"-Fill a 2L flask with about 450 mL of ddH20.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":28,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"688hb","text":"-Add 4 mL of CaCl2solution to the bottle. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":5,"length":4},{"style":"sub","offset":17,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bjao1","text":"-Add 4 mL of MgCl2solution to the bottle. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":5,"length":4},{"style":"sub","offset":17,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5ack1","text":"-Add 5.02 g of glucose (final concentration of 13.93 mM)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":5,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"33j71","text":"-Add 200 mL of a 10X stock aCSF solution.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":5,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6gjvi","text":"-Swirl mixture around well by hand for a few seconds.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2fd18","text":"-Fill remainder of flask to 2 L with ddH20.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":28,"length":3}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"euf4b","text":"-Carbogenate solution for at least 10 minutes before using.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c0hdd","text":"Using continuously carbogenated 1x aCSF: §Fill a small slice holding chamber with the 1x aCSF and add 5 mM of L-glutathione at approximately 1:1000x and 1 mM of Na-Pyruvate at 1:300x.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":102,"length":4},{"style":"bold","offset":141,"length":7},{"style":"bold","offset":153,"length":8},{"style":"bold","offset":176,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3lrh3","text":"-Set the chamber aside near a 37 °C heated water bath while the solution inside the holding chamber is continuously carbogenated.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":30,"length":5}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7bf6r","text":"-Additionally, decant approximately 100 mL of 1X aCSF into a small glass beaker kept cold on ice while carbogenated (to be use for perfusate)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":36,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bfqqn","text":"Next, decant approximately 100 mL of the 1X solution into a 300 mL L plastic bucket and place the bucket in a −20 °Cfreezer for 70—80 minutes. This solution is to be used for cutting brain tissues and should be frozen over but not frozen solid. After taking the bucket out from freezer:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":27,"length":6},{"style":"bold","offset":60,"length":6},{"style":"bold","offset":110,"length":6},{"style":"bold","offset":128,"length":13}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cql0d","text":"-Using a large spatula, break up ice and stir into a slurry.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6dhtk","text":"-Add approximately 100 mL of 1X aCSF kept at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":19,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"pehn","text":"-Mix solution with a handheld blender until forming an easily flowing slush.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"966mn","text":"-Keep the bucket of the 1x aCSF slush cutting solution on ice while being carbogenated.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7tc0t","text":"-The slush solution should consist of approximately one fifths of liquid solution and be settled to the bottom of the bucket. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ftj0i","text":"Overdose the mouse with a 1 mLintraperitoneallyinjection of a 150 mg/kg ketamine and 30 mg/kg xylamzine mix. While mouse is overdosing: place the slice chamber in a heated water bath set to 37 °C (water in the bath should come up the side of the chamber to approximately the same height as the aCSF). Next, after mouse is completely anesthetized:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":26,"length":4},{"style":"bold","offset":62,"length":41},{"style":"bold","offset":190,"length":5}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a71mo","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fqpk5","text":"-Transcardially perfuse mouse with the ice-cold 1x aCSF.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bo599","text":"-Rapidly decapitate and extract brain in 1x aCSF slush.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5ebdm","text":"-Using razor blade, cut brain down the midline.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7gm95","text":"-Glue brain medial side down on cutting block and place block quickly into cutting chamber of a Vibratome.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fp1eg","text":"-Fill cutting chamber with aCSF slush solution, kept continuously carbogenated in chamber.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ctakg","text":"-Cut slices at 240 µmthick","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":15,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fcsat","text":"-Quickly transfer each cut slice into hold chamber kept in heated bath.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5s332","text":"-Remove holding chamber from bath 30 minutes after last slice transfer is made.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"19mkb","text":"-Allow holding chamber to equilibrate to room temperature (approximately 20 minutes) before transferring slices to recording chamber of electrophysiological rig.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"57kho","text":"Using a pipette puller, glass pipettes should be pulled to ensure a pipette resistance of 3.2—3.8 MΩ. For whole-cell voltage clamp recordings, a KMeSO4 solution is used containing the following:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":90,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7778j","text":"-KMeSO4: 135 mM","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":9,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4fmrh","text":"-KCl: 5 mM","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":6,"length":4}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7kcd4","text":"-CaCl2: 0.5 mM","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":8,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a0d0t","text":"-HEPES: 5 mM","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":8,"length":4}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9eidu","text":"-EGTA-K: 5 mM","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":9,"length":4}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"esfdt","text":"-ATP-Mg: 2 mM","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":9,"length":4}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8glud","text":"-GTP-Na: 0.5 mM","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":9,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8sis","text":"-Biocytin: 0.20% (w/v in grams)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4jasr","text":"Transferred slices in recording chamber are continuously perfused with 1x aCSF that is kept at room temperature and continuously carbogenated. Neurons for recording are identified and recorded as follows:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"40su7","text":"-Pipettes are backfilled with KMeSO4 solution and inserted into headstage of amplifier. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cfma8","text":"-Pipettes are then pressurized to approximately 56 millibars.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":48,"length":12}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2l5ct","text":"-Pipettes area offset before cell attachment.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8gj3k","text":"-Neurons are clamped at —80 mV before whole-cell access is achieved.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":24,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7ang7","text":"Stimulus generation and data acquisition are performed using an amplifier (Molecular Devices), a digitizer (Molecular Devices), and pClamp (Molecular Devices). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5d63a","text":"For current-clamp recordings","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":28},{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":0,"length":28}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5bntb","text":"Adjust the amplifier bridge circuit to compensate for electrode resistance and subsequently monitor it. Filter the signals at 1 kHz and digitize them at 10 kHz.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5ffa8","text":"KMeSO4and Na2-GTP were from ICN Biomedicals and Roche, respectively. All other reagents were obtained from Sigma-Aldrich.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":121},{"style":"sub","offset":5,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":12,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"82uug","text":"Examine the frequency-current (F-I) relationship of each cell with current-clamp recordings as follows.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ctk5f","text":"-Apply a series of 500 ms current steps of n beginning at −150 pA and incremented at 25 pA for each consecutive sweep.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2uuev","text":"  -A 30 second intertrial interval is used.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":5,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9l5e4","text":"  -The current steps are continued until depolarization block is reached.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b4rcc","text":"  -Monitor resting membrane potential was monitored for stability, and exclude cells that varied 20% from mean baseline from the analysis. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"vpth","text":"-Perform electrical stimulation using parallel bipolar tungsten electrodes (FHC) placed in layer 5 of the cortex. ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"499ki","text":"-Adjust stimulus width and intensity via a constant current stimulator (Digitimer) to evoke a first excitatory postsynaptic current (EPSC) with an amplitude of 200–400 pA in the presence of the GABAAreceptor antagonist SR95531 (10 µM) and CGP55845 (1 µM). ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":198,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bgqpk","text":"-Monitor whole-cell access was monitored with a −5 mV pulse throughout the recording. Determine off line the membrane capacitance (Cm) as Cm = Qt * Vtest, where Qt was calculated as the integral of the transient current elicited by Vtest, a 10 mV voltage step. ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":144,"length":2},{"style":"sub","offset":149,"length":4},{"style":"sub","offset":233,"length":4}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fi4mg","text":"-Take the average of the ratios of the second EPSC amplitude to the first EPSC amplitude for each recording sweep to calculate the paired-pulse ratio (PPR) for a given cell ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"adp8r","text":"-Exclude data if the series resistance of the patch pipette differed by \u003e 20% between the two recordings. ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
